OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1782227912
OL,3,CBlacksmith alters hours due to
OL,4,Cheatwave as rare red weather warning
OL,5,Capproaches
OL,7,FA blacksmith from Berkshire is
OL,8,Faltering his working hours as high
OL,9,Ftemperatures continue.
OL,11,FJohn Lovelock, from Wokingham, says he
OL,12,Fstarts earlier when the weather is so
OL,13,Fhot to take account of the unusual
OL,14,Fconditions.
OL,16,FIt comes as the Met Office issued a
OL,17,Frare red weather warning for parts of
OL,18,Fthe UK between 9am on Wednesday (24
OL,19,FJune) and 9pm on Thursday (25 June),
OL,20,Fincluding areas of the South East.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1782227912
OL,3,CBlacksmith alters hours due to
OL,4,Cheatwave as rare red weather warning
OL,5,Capproaches
OL,7,FMany schools are also preparing to
OL,8,Feither shut early or close entirely
OL,9,Fdue to the weather.
OL,11,FDiscussing the changes he makes in hot
OL,12,Fweather such as this, Mr Lovelock
OL,13,Fsaid: "We are conscious of the heat,
OL,14,Fso we will start at 6 in the morning,
OL,15,Ffinish at 2(pm).
OL,17,F"Sometimes if it's just a one day
OL,18,Fthing, we've got a job that is hard
OL,19,Fwork and a bit more heat involved, we
OL,20,Fmay just finish early.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1782227912
OL,3,CBlacksmith alters hours due to
OL,4,Cheatwave as rare red weather warning
OL,5,Capproaches
OL,7,F"But you have to be mindful of the
OL,8,Fheat and keep hydrated because
OL,9,Fotherwise you can just forget yourself
OL,10,Fand carry on.
OL,12,F"Before you know it you're dripping in
OL,13,Fsweat and it's no good for anyone."
OL,15,FContrasting the heatwave with the high
OL,16,Ftemperatures he experiences inside as
OL,17,Fpart of his line of work, Mr Lovelock
OL,18,Fcontinued: "When it's hot weather, you
OL,19,Fhave no control, so you have to be
OL,20,Fmindful of how you're going to react
OL,21,Fand cope with that hot weather.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1782227912
OL,3,CBlacksmith alters hours due to
OL,4,Cheatwave as rare red weather warning
OL,5,Capproaches
OL,7,F"If it's hot because you're forging
OL,8,Fand blacksmithing, then you're more in
OL,9,Fcontrol.
OL,11,F"So then you can stop, leave the job
OL,12,Ffor five minutes, get a water break
OL,13,Fand come back to it.
OL,15,F"But when it's hot weather like this,
OL,16,Fyou don't have the opportunity to do
OL,17,Fthat."
OL,19,FMr Lovelock is not the only Berkshire
OL,20,Fbusiness making changes due to the
OL,21,Fheat.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1782227912
OL,3,CBlacksmith alters hours due to
OL,4,Cheatwave as rare red weather warning
OL,5,Capproaches
OL,7,FBrew Coffee Bar in Bracknell is taking
OL,8,Fhot food off the menu to account for
OL,9,Fthe soaring temperatures.
OL,11,FOwner Jem Piggott explained: "We've
OL,12,Fgot a very hot potato oven behind
OL,13,Fthere, a panini press and an oven
OL,14,Fthat's normally on full blast.
OL,16,F"So this week we've taken that out of
OL,17,Fthe equation, we've turned all the
OL,18,Ffans on, we've got the windows open.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1782227912
OL,3,CBlacksmith alters hours due to
OL,4,Cheatwave as rare red weather warning
OL,5,Capproaches
OL,7,F"So yeah, it's going to be cold food
OL,8,Fonly, cold drinks, cake, that kind of
OL,9,Fthing."
OL,11,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,12,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,13,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,14,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,15,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,16,Fbelow...
